main event: A highway patrolman spotted a very bright, pulsating red and green object in the sky over South Dakota in 1966.
interesting points: The object was so bright that the observers could not make out its exact shape.
Two different observers estimated the size of the object to be between the size of a dime and a quarter.
The object had a brilliant red color with a pulsating green light above the red.
The object made a buzzing sound for about 5 seconds.
The object was observed for about 1.5 hours, traveling in an up and down pattern at a very high speed.
sighted object: a very bright, pulsating red and green object in the sky
witnesses: two highway patrolmen, described as very reliable observers
